# FFmpegWrapper Project Conventions

## Stack

- Python 3.9+, PySide6 (Qt), OpenAI SDK
- GUI: manual widget layouts (no QML)
- Background work: QThread + QObject.moveToThread()
- Settings: dataclass + JSON at ~/.ffmpeg_app_settings.json
- Build: PyInstaller, codesign, notarytool (macOS)

## Source Layout

- All app code in `src/ffmpeg_app/`
- Tests in `tests/` (pytest, run with `PYTHONPATH=src`)
- PyInstaller entry: `app_entry.py`
- Dev entry: `PYTHONPATH=src python -m ffmpeg_app.main`

## Module Responsibilities

| Module | Owns |
|--------|------|
| `ui.py` | All GUI widgets, dialogs, workers |
| `settings.py` | AppSettings dataclass, load/save, constants |
| `options.py` | FFmpegOptions, arg building, output path |
| `ffmpeg_runner.py` | Subprocess execution, cancel |
| `transcriber.py` | Audio extraction, Deepgram API |
| `notes_generator.py` | OpenAI Responses API |

## Coding Standards

- Use `from __future__ import annotations` in every module
- Type hints on all function signatures
- Dataclasses for structured data (settings, options)
- No inline comments that just narrate what code does
- Keep API keys in settings, never hardcode
- New deps go in both `requirements.txt` and `pyproject.toml`
- After adding a hidden import, update `hiddenimports` in `pyinstaller-macos.spec`
